        <div class="page-header-info">
            <h1>
                Diaspora
            </h1>
            <p class="minimize">Diaspora Jewry is the collective name for the Jewish communities outside of the Land of Israel. Historically, these communities go back to big historical events like the Babylonian exile, the siege of Jerusalem and the expulsion from Spain. Today, the biggest Diaspora communities exist in the United States, France, Canada, the UK and Russia.</p>
        </div>

